        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:31PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Maxton, or near Laurinburg, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Maxton, Antioch, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg, and
Laurel Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
